article.description: — Marcus Domask registered 17 points, five assists and three blocks as Southern Illinois beat North Dakota 62-50 on Friday. Ben Harvey added 12 points and nine rebounds for the Salukis, and Anthony D'Avanzo chipped in 11 points and eight rebounds.
article.headline: Domask, Harvey lead S. Illinois past North Dakota 62-50
article.linkText: Domask, Harvey lead S. Illinois past North Dakota 62-50
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. -- — Marcus Domask registered 17 points, five assists and three blocks as Southern Illinois beat North Dakota 62-50 on Friday. Ben Harvey added 12 points and nine rebounds for the Salukis, and Anthony D’Avanzo chipped in 11 points and eight rebounds. Lance Jones had seven assists for Southern Illinois (5-0), which earned its fifth consecutive victory to open the season. Filip Rebraca had 11 points and eight rebounds for the Fighting Hawks (1-7), whose losing streak reached four games. Tyree Ihenacho added seven assists. The Salukis defeated North Dakota 85-64 last Thursday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
